result.execSummary:
The defendant Timothy D Williams was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).
  • Retail Theft - Alter Price (<=$500) [Modifiers: as a Party to a Crime], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.50(1m)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

(Day 2 consolidated for trial) Defendant Timothy D Williams in court with attorney Russell J. A. Jones.   Defendant Carresha C Goodlow in court with attorney Eamon Collins Guerin. Jeffrey A Sisley appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Jury brought into courtroom. State calls T.S. called to stand, sworn, examination continues. Cross examination by Attorney Jones. Cross examination by Attorney Guerin. Redirect. Recross by Attorney Jones. Recess. Recalled, Appearances same. Jury returns to courtroom. State calls Sgt. Robert Meyer sworn & testified. Cross examination by Attorney Jones. Cross examination by Attorney Guerin. Redirect. State calls Officer Matthew Caswell, sworn and testified. Cross examination by Attorney Jones. Cross examination by Attorney Guerin. Recess.  Recalled, appearances same, jury not present. Statements placed on record with next witness. Officer Neese sworn and testified outside the presence of the jury. Cross by Attorney Jones.  Jury returns to courtroom. State calls Officer Emily Neese sworn & testified. Cross examination by Attorney Jones. Cross examination by Attorney Guerin. Redirect. Recross. Written Stipulation by parties read to jury. State rests. Jury excused from courtroom. Attorney Jones moves to dismiss. Attorney Guerin makes separate motion to dismiss. Response by State. Court denies both motions. Court's collequy as to right to testify with both defendants. Jury instruction conference appearances by Mr Williams and Ms Goodlow waived. 12:30 Recess for lunch. 1:30 Recalled, appearances same. Final review of instructions/verdicts. Jury called to courtroom. Defense Attorney Jones rests without testimony.  Defense Attorney Guerin rests without testimony. Jury instructions read by court. Closing argument by State. Closing argument by Attorney Guerin. Closing argument by Attorney Jones. Rebuttal by State. Final instructions by the court. Oath to bailiff. 2:55 Jury excused to deliberate. Attorney Jones moves for directed verdict. Attorney Guerin moves for directed verdict. Response by State. Denied by Court. Recess. 3:40 Recalled, appearances same. Jury returns to courtroom. Jury foreperson identified. Verdicts read by court. Jury polled. Jury thanked & excused. State asks for judgment on the verdicts. Granted on all 3 verdicts. All bail revoked for both defendants and remanded into custody of the sheriff. Argument by counsel as to remand. Denied for both defendants.
